// LAUNCH OPTIONS


// current CSGO Linux:
gamemoderun RADV_PERFTEST=aco LP_NUM_THREADS=5 AMD_DEBUG=nodcc,nodma %command% -high -nojoy -noaafonts -novid -nofxaa -cl_forcepreload 1 -sv_forcepreload 1 -language bananagaming -threads 5 -tickrate 128 +clientport 27027

// Windows:
-high -nojoy -nofxaa -noaafonts -novid -language bananagaming -threads 5 -tickrate 128 +clientport 27027


// NOTE: the %command% environment options apply to the launch string and may prevent launch with some hardware eg nvidia GPUs
// some of these are likely pointless as the drivers are constantly in development
//
// if more than one computer is running steam on your local network, set "+clientport 27027" to anything
// between and including 27005 and 27032, excluding 27020 and any number in use on another local machine (27005 is default)
//
// https://support.steampowered.com/kb_article.php?ref=6370-QPHJ-3567


// "AMD_DEBUG=nodcc,nodma,zerovram %command%" // may prevent random artifacting on some GPUs, can hurt or help performance
// "LP_NUM_THREADS=6 %command%" // threads for rendering. default = CPU core count, reduce number to free up CPU eg for screen recording
// "-language bananagaming" // enables that text color mod if installed
// "gamemoderun %command%" // invoke Feral's gamemode daemon. I use it to set niceness etc.
//                         // enabling performance CPU governer is also beneficial, I use corectrl for that + GPU control
//
//
// mesa_no_error=true %command% // disables GL error handling, allows fancy gloves to render correctly but may cause crashing on some maps eg overpass
// "strangle 250 %command%" // external FPS-limiter for Linux (libstrangle) I tested briefly, this one isn't capped but best to use the in-game limiter
//
// __GL_FSAA_MODE=0 %command%" %command%" // nvidia gl option 
// "__GL_THREADED_OPTIMIZATIONS=1 %command%" // nvidia gl option, not needed, included in the csgo.sh file
// "MESA_GL_VERSION_OVERRIDE=4.6 MESA_GLSL_VERSION_OVERRIDE=460" %command%" // enable higher GL version, not needed for csgo
//
// R600_DEBUG=nodcc,nodma,zerovram // old r600 driver option, replaced with AMD_DEBUG
// "GLX_EXT_swap_control_tear=0 tearfree=0 EnablePageFlip=0 SwapBuffersWait=0 vblank_mode=0 %command%" // old DRI-2 options
// 
// -nojoy // disables joypad detection. can prevent performance issues and even crashing on some systems
//
//
// Linux-focused optimisation guide:
//
// https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1502890492


// HL1 Linux, goldsrc games
AMD_DEBUG=nodcc,nodma,zerovram %command% -novid +exec hl1exec.cfg

// HL2 Linux, old Source games
LP_NUM_THREADS=3 gamemoderun AMD_DEBUG=nodcc,nodma,zerovram __GL_THREADED_OPTIMIZATIONS=1 %command% -novid +exec hl2exec
